args: Ahhh, there's the sweet mountain air\nI've been missing!
Er, you okay back there, Cleo?\nShould we take another break?
No, I'm fine... If we keep to my pace,\nthe sun will set before we're able to\ndo any proper cooking.
(Cleo's not much for mountain climbing,\nis she?)
(And yet, she's still come on this selfish\nlittle quest to improve my cooking skills.)
That'll be quite unnecessary. You have\nplenty enough to lug around on your own.
Look, we've come all this way, right?\nLet's at least try to have some fun\non the last stretch up the mountain.
That's very kind, Mitsuba, thank you.\nI think I shall take you up on it.
We picked a pretty great spot hereâ€”\nthere's a natural windbreak to keep us\nwarm, and plenty of sunlight as well.
Now that we have our campsite,\nwe should start foraging for ingredients.
I hear one can find a good number\nof trout in the nearby rivers.
Alberia has trout? I had no idea...\nWelp, let's get some hooks baited!
These river fish are cautious ones,\naren't they? I think they may have\nnoticed us and hid themselves away.
If that's the case, we could drop our lines\nall night long and still come up empty.
Er, Mitsuba? What are you doing with\nthat very large knife?
I am a chef, and this knife is my weapon.\nHundreds and thousands of fish have\nbent to my will before it.
And now I will use it to make the trout\nthat lurk in this river yield as well!

Whether in the mountains or a kitchen,
whether atop a cutting board or in the
cool shadow of a mighty boulder,
the grit of a chef is undying! HAHHH!
You caught a hidden trout\nwith your KNIFE?!
I told you my knife skills are unmatched!
That was more akin to a bear\ncatching salmon...
Anyway, now that we've got this fish,\nlet's pick some edible plants on the way\nback and get to cooking!
Geez, there are so many pla... Hmm?
Oh my gosh, are those alpine leeks?!\nThere's so MANY of them!
Are you referring to the ramsons there?
Ramsons, eh? Huh, you're right.\nThey LOOK like alpine leeks, but they're\nactually something different entirely.

*sniff* Wow, they even SMELL the same.
Actually, this could be a great discovery!
Alpine leeks are super rare, but these
could make the perfect substitution.
I could use them in salads, tempura,\nstir-fry... Heck, in practically everything!\nAnd this place is just chock FULL of 'em!
*sigh* I don't know if it's quite THAT\nexciting, but she certainly seems happy\nin her own little world there.
...Mitsuba? The sun is setting. I know\nyou are in a mad daze at the moment,\nbut do try to retain a bit of control.
But I NEED this stuff, Cleo! I'm seriously\ngonna start using it in everything I cook\nfrom now on!
Yes yes, it truly is a miracle.\nNow let's return to camp and cook.
The sun's all the way down now,\nso let's hurry and get to cooking.
Time to bust out the pot we bought\nback in the rokkan village.
This outdoor cooking trip is absolutely\ngoing to give me the inspiration I need to\nredefine my cooking!
